Clinical Diagnosis: Suspicious mass in the upper outer quadrant of the left breast.

Specimen: Left breast biopsy.

Macroscopic Description: Firm, irregular mass measuring 3.8 cm, located 1.2 cm from the nearest surgical margin.

Microscopic Description: Invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC), grade 2, with gland-forming structures, moderate nuclear pleomorphism, high mitotic rate, and lymphovascular invasion. Surrounding tissue shows ductal carcinoma in situ (DCIS) without significant skin or chest wall involvement.

Immunohistochemistry: ER positive (85%), PR positive (60%), HER2/neu negative (1+), Ki-67 at 30%.

Pathological Staging: T2 (Tumor > 2 cm but ≤ 5 cm), N1 (Metastasis to 1-3 axillary lymph nodes), M0 (No distant metastasis).

Final Pathologic Stage: IIB.

Additional Findings: Lymphovascular invasion present, surgical margins clear by 1.2 cm.", "generatedTime": "2024-10-18 07:04:55.659131", "metadata": {"model": "gpt-4o", "modelVersion": "2023-12-01-preview", "promptId": "ONCO_RES_SUMMARY_L2_PROMPT", "promptVersion": "1"}}}}
